Fisher of souls and father of Kenya’s Sacco movement             Jacinta Mutura  04th Aug 2019 09:45:58 GMT +0300 Jacinta Mutura  04th Aug 2019 09:45:58 GMT +0300 Jacinta Mutura   Fr Joakim Getonga at his office in Murang'a Town,on May 27, 2019. Gitonga started the first registered Sacco in Kenya,1964, Mariira Parish Co-operative Savings and Credit Society. He was given dispensation from priestly obligations and allowed to marry by Pope John Paul 11, in 1975. [Kibata Kihu/Standard]   Fr Joakim Getonga at his office in Murang'a Town,on May 27, 2019. Gitonga started the first registered Sacco in Kenya,1964, Mariira Parish Co-operative Savings and Credit Society. He was given dispensation from priestly obligations and allowed to marry by Pope John Paul 11, in 1975. [Kibata Kihu/Standard] Fr Joakim Getonga at his office in Murang'a Town,on May 27, 2019. Gitonga started the first registered Sacco in Kenya,1964, Mariira Parish Co-operative Savings and Credit Society. He was given dispensation from priestly obligations and allowed to marry by Pope John Paul 11, in 1975. [Kibata Kihu/Standard] Fr Joakim Getonga at his office in Murang'a Town,on May 27, 2019. Gitonga started the first registered Sacco in Kenya,1964, Mariira Parish Co-operative Savings and Credit Society. He was given dispensation from priestly obligations and allowed to marry by Pope John Paul 11, in 1975.     Cultural erosion  SEE ALSO :Priest and father of cooperative movement SEE ALSO : Priest and father of cooperative movement                        Africa’s best        We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. HERE Related Topics Joachim Getonga Kikuyu Council of 